  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "DCGAN provides a meaningful solution in terms of a stable architecture as compared to a vanilla GAN.",
    "However, DCGAN lacks in generating diverse, realistic, and free of artifacts images which are fundamental challenges that need more advanced solutions.",
    "In vanilla GAN, the generator produces synthetic images only based on latent input z which is considered to be limited information for high-performance image synthesis.",
    "Authors Mirza and Osindero (2014) proposed an idea of conditional GAN that utilizes additional information y together with the random vector input z as well as input to the discriminator.",
    "The y can be a class label or any other conditional information that acts as an additional information feed to the generator as well as the discriminator."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Authors Mirza and Osindero (2014) proposed an idea of conditional GAN that utilizes additional information y together with the random vector input z as well as input to the discriminator."
  ]
